<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,827,1467,1492]" box="[151,827,1467,1492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<treatmentCitationGroup box="[151,827,1467,1492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<treatmentCitation author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[151,823,1467,1492]" page="445" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" year="2016">
<taxonomicName authority="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, 2016: 445" authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityPageNumber="445" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,823,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis box="[151,373,1468,1492]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Belonuchus cifuentesi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[379,823,1467,1492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="444 - 450" refId="ref113932" refString="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L. (2016) A new Mexican species of Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 4083 (3), 444 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4083.3.8" type="journal article" year="2016">Rodríguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, 2016: 445</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1538,2032]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
This species has been recently described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[639,1081,1538,1565]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="444 - 450" refId="ref113932" refString="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L. (2016) A new Mexican species of Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 4083 (3), 444 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4083.3.8" type="journal article" year="2016">Rodríguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia (2016)</bibRefCitation>
; therefore, a redescription is not necessary. We only include some taxonomic comments and some illustrations of diagnostic structures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1538,2032]" lastBlockId="71.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,459,1609,1636]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Taxonomic comments</emphasis>
. This species can be confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1840" box="[864,993,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dichrous">
<emphasis box="[864,993,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. dichrous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solsky" authorityYear="1870" box="[1048,1203,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis box="[1048,1203,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The means of separation from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1840" box="[288,418,1646,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dichrous">
<emphasis box="[288,418,1646,1672]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. dichrous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mentioned in the taxonomic comments of that species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1082,1329,1646,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis box="[1082,1329,1646,1672]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Belonuchus cifuentesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solsky" authorityYear="1870" box="[311,468,1682,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis box="[311,468,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the legs and first two visible abdominal segments reddish as elytra, male genital sternite very elongate (3.28 times longer than wide), aedeagus large (
<quantity box="[1031,1124,1718,1744]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
), oval-elongate shape, with apex subacute (
<figureCitation box="[322,417,1754,1780]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="118.[151,250,1786,1810]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,193,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-25@118.[151,1436,181,1762]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURE 24. Ventral (left) and lateral (right) view (except e) of the aedeagus of: a) Belonuchus rufiventris, b) B. xanthomelas (at center, detail of the apex of the median lobe), c) B. ephippiatus, d) B. moroni, e) B. cifuentesi (left: detail of paramere, right: ventral view; from Rodríguez and Navarrete-Heredia, 2016), f) B. dichrous, g) B. flavipennis, h) B. aenigmaticus, i) B. iridescens, j) B. nigerrimus, k) B. optatus, l) B. platypterus. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (all figures, except e)." pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 24e</figureCitation>
). While 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solsky" authorityYear="1870" box="[509,661,1754,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis box="[509,661,1754,1780]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has legs and all abdomen black, except anterior border of sixth visible segment, male genital sternite short (2.21 times longer than wide), small aedeagus (
<quantity box="[1083,1188,1790,1816]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="1.13">1.13 mm</quantity>
), with elongate shape, convex apex, slightly acute in ventral view and moderately acute in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1071,1171,1826,1852]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="118.[151,250,1786,1810]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,193,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-25@118.[151,1436,181,1762]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURE 24. Ventral (left) and lateral (right) view (except e) of the aedeagus of: a) Belonuchus rufiventris, b) B. xanthomelas (at center, detail of the apex of the median lobe), c) B. ephippiatus, d) B. moroni, e) B. cifuentesi (left: detail of paramere, right: ventral view; from Rodríguez and Navarrete-Heredia, 2016), f) B. dichrous, g) B. flavipennis, h) B. aenigmaticus, i) B. iridescens, j) B. nigerrimus, k) B. optatus, l) B. platypterus. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (all figures, except e)." pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1124,1171,1826,1852]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.4" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="g" value="24.0">24g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1190,1436,1826,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis box="[1190,1436,1826,1852]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Belonuchus cifuentesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also can be confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[442,589,1863,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arizonicus">
<emphasis box="[442,589,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. arizonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According with 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[779,1276,1862,1889]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="444 - 450" refId="ref113932" refString="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L. (2016) A new Mexican species of Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 4083 (3), 444 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4083.3.8" type="journal article" year="2016">Rodríguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia (2016: 450)</bibRefCitation>
, “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1299,1436,1862,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. cifuentesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the black abdominal segments from tergite V, the pleurites VI and VIII are black in more than half of specimens, antennomeres pubescent, tempora less than twice as long as the length of the eyes, the first 4 antennomeres are longer than width, anterior corners and pronotal hypomera reddish-brown, frons with wide fovea and with a longitudinal impression, dorsal surface with scattered umbilicate punctures, first three antennomeres bearing only sparse strong setae, outer antennomeres (4–11) with microtrichia and long setae, profemur with two lines of spines of irregular size, metafemur with two lines of small and strong spines; tibiae with several spines; tarsi filiform, first and fifth tarsomeres longer than each one of the second to fourth, aedeagus small, narrow and elongate, median lobe subparallel-sided to slightly, evenly narrowed toward obtuse apex and smaller than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[1086,1234,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arizonicus">
<emphasis box="[1086,1234,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">B. arizonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1249,1317,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="103.[151,250,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[199,1392,191,1872]" captionTargetId="figure-19@103.[184,1404,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="FIGURE 9. Dorsal view of males of: a) Belonuchus sp. Q, b) B. cyanipennis (holotype), c) B. godmani. Head of B. dichrous showing the temporal carina (red arrow): d) lateral view (male), e) dorsal view (male). Dorsal view of the mandibles of males of: f) B. platypterus, g) B. viridipennis. Mandibles of Belonuchus sp. Q (male): h) dorsal view, i) ventral view. Antennae of males of: j) B. godmani, k) B. cyanipennis. Scale bars = 2.5 mm." pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
)”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
